> the symbol will resolve to the same object_id every time across systems and processes. If you spin up irb and type :foo.object_id you will see 1092508.<p>object_id for symbols is not consistent across processes.<p><pre><code>   % ruby -e &quot;p :foo.object_id&quot;
   396968
   % ruby -e &quot;p :bar.object_id&quot;
   396968
   % ruby -e &quot;:bar; p :foo.object_id&quot;
   397128
</code></pre>
You&#x27;re getting 1092508 consistently not because it&#x27;s :foo but because it&#x27;s the next object_id available for a symbol after all the ones created during IRB startup.
